  "eprint": {
    "title": "Improved preprocessing for the Crossbred algorithm and application to the MQ problem",
    "authors": [
      {
        "name": "Damien Vidal",
        "email": "vidal@u-picardie",
        "affiliation": ""
      },
      {
        "name": "Claire Delaplace",
        "email": "delaplace@u-picardie",
        "affiliation": ""
      },
      {
        "name": "Sorina Ionica",
        "email": "ionica@uvsq",
        "affiliation": ""
      }
    ],
    "abstract": "First, we correct certain omissions in the literature on the complexity analysis of Crossbred and give a full analysis of this algorithm. \r\nSecondly, we propose a criterion to reduce the number of polynomials generated in the preprocessing step for a set of admissible parameters $D$, $d$ and $k$, whenever this step of the algorithm produces more polynomials than necessary. We conclude by applying this criterion to the security of MQOM.",
    "keywords": [
      "multivariate cryptography",
      "MQ problem",
      "Gröbner basis algorithm",
      "MQOM"
    ],
    "category": "Attacks and cryptanalysis",
    "publication_info": "Preprint.",
    "last_updated": "2026-02-23",
